1 B. Limitations on GLP-1 medications for drug manufacturers shall apply to
2 any health coverage plan for whom a provider issues a prescription, regardless of the
3 insured's specific medical condition or diagnosis.
4 (1) A health coverage plan shall not impose a cost-sharing provision for
5 GLP-1 medications in the health coverage plan's formulary if the total amount the
6 insured is required to pay exceeds two hundred dollars per prescription for a
7 thirty-day supply, regardless of the amount or type of GLP-1 medication needed to
8 fill the insured's prescription.
9 Section 2. Part IX of Chapter 5-E title 40 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
10 comprised of R.S. 40:1259.11, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 §1259.11 GLP-1 medications; Medicaid coverage
12 A. The Louisiana Medicaid program shall make available to persons who are
13 eligible for Medicaid benefits under Title XIX of the Social Security Act, 42 U.S.C.
14 1396 et seq., coverage benefits for GLP-1 medications regardless of the enrollee's
15 specific medical condition or diagnosis, when a provider issues a prescription.
16 B. The Louisiana Department of Health may seek approval of a federal
17 Medicaid waiver and state plan amendments as may be necessary to implement the
18 provisions of this Section.
