HB 920 Original 2026 Regular Session Jordan
Abstract: Limits drug manufacturers pricing of 30-day supply of GLP-1 medications for
health insurance plans. Extends GLP-1 medication coverage to Medicaid, Office of
Group Benefits (OGB), and other health plans regardless of the insured's medical
condition or diagnosis.
Proposed law prohibits health coverage plans from charging an insured or enrollee more than
$200 for a 30-day supply of GLP-1 medications.
Proposed law extends GLP-1 medication coverage to Medicaid, OGB, and other health plans
regardless of the enrollee's or insured's medical condition or diagnosis.
(Adds R.S. 22:1034.2 and R.S. 40:1259.11)
